gration: EEA Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to his Department’s document entitled EU Settlement Scheme: Looked After Children and Care Leavers. Local Authority and Health and Social Care Trusts Guidance, when applications are due under the scheme in the event of the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and what the status would be of children who are EEA citizens under care orders or care leavers in the event the UK leaves the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","244112"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121459","Department for Transport","false","2019-04-23","<p>A response to the Hon Member’s letter about Hammersmith Bridge was sent to his office on 10 April.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-04-23T15:43:01.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121459/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121459/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121459/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-04-11","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he plans to respond to the correspondence of 4 March 2019 from the hon. Member for Richmond Park on Hammersmith Bridge.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","244072"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121460","Department for Transport","false","2019-04-24","<p>Maintenance on Hammersmith Bridge is the responsibility of the London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham. It is for the Council to determine their road maintenance programme.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-04-24T14:26:28.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121460/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121460/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121460/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-04-11","Hammersmith Bridge","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will take steps to ensure that Hammersmith Bridge can safely reopen as soon as possible.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","244073"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121461","Department for International Trade","false","2019-04-25","<p>The UK is working closely with the EU and European partners to support a negotiated settlement to the Airbus and Boeing disputes. Through the EU, we are challenging in the WTO the US’s claim that it is entitled to impose retaliatory tariffs on the UK. However, it would not be appropriate for the UK to make representations to the US on specific products whilst we are contesting the right of the US to impose any tariffs at all.</p><p> </p><p>We are clear that a tariff war would not be in the interests of UK, EU or US industry. We agree with EU and others that we do not want to see the disputes escalate further. The UK will continue to work closely with the EU on next steps.</p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery","244168","2019-04-25T08:50:30.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121461/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121461/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121461/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-04-11","Ceramics: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what representations he has made to the US to oppose retaliatory duties of up to 100 per cent against British ceramic products.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","244167"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121462","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-04-24","<p>We have not made an assessment of this nature, as it is wrong to attribute any change in rent arrears solely to Universal Credit. The initial analytical work we have carried out with a single housing provider suggests that many tenants are arriving on Universal Credit with pre-existing rent arrears, that their arrears tend to increase prior to making a claim for Universal Credit, and that Universal Credit actually appears to be helping to clear arrears over time. We are currently extending this analysis to include a number of housing providers. It will be published when completed. Furthermore, according to latest figures (November 2018) only about 8% of social rented households were on Universal Credit; therefore it is difficult to see how a national trend can be attributed to Universal Credit.</p><p> </p><p>We have responded to concerns in this area by putting a number of safeguards in place - 100% advances repayable over 12 months, increasing to 16 months in October 2021; a two-week Transition to Universal Credit Housing Payment; a new Help to Claim service; and Managed Payment to Landlord Arrangements, which allow for payments direct to the landlord if the tenant is likely to have difficulty in managing their rent payments, is unlikely to pay their rent or is in rent arrears equivalent to eight weeks.</p>","Colchester","Will Quince",,"2019-04-24T10:17:09.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121462/answer","Biography information for Will Quince","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121462/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121462/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-04-11","Universal Credit: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment she had made of the effect of the roll out of universal credit on levels of rent arrears in the London borough of Croydon.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","244110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121463","Home Office","false","2019-04-24","<p>It is our long-standing policy not to provide detailed information on the security arrangements for individuals. To do so could compromise the integrity of those arrangements and affect the security of the individuals concerned. This includes numbers related to those in receipt of protection measures.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2019-04-24T11:55:14.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121463/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121463/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121463/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-04-11","Foreign Nationals: Saudi Arabia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many Saudi Arabian citizens or former Saudi Arabian citizens have been put under police protection in the UK since 2015; and how many of those have been put under police protection from October 2018 until now.","false","Biography information for Crispin Blunt","Reigate","Crispin Blunt","243988"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121464","Department for Transport","false","2019-04-24","<p>Local authorities are independent bodies. Section 108, Part 2 of the Transport Act 2000 (as amended by the Local Transport Act 2008) sets out that each local transport authority must (a) develop policies for the promotion and encouragement of safe, integrated, efficient and economic transport to, from and within their area, and (b) carry out their functions so as to implement those policies. The Act also defines transport as, among other things, the transport required to meet the needs of persons living or working in the authority’s area, or visiting or travelling through that area<strong>.</strong></p><p>The Department collaborates closely with local authorities on a range of issues. However, in London, Transport for London is best placed to facilitate any additional coordination of transport issues between Boroughs that may be considered necessary.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-04-24T14:13:05.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121464/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121464/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121464/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-04-11","Local Government: Cooperation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to ensure that local authorities work together in ensuring that key routes between council areas, such as bridges, remain safe and accessible to the public.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","244074"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121465","Department for International Trade","false","2019-04-25","<p>The UK is working closely with the EU and European partners to support a negotiated settlement to the Airbus and Boeing disputes. Through the EU, we are challenging in the WTO the US’s claim that it is entitled to impose retaliatory tariffs on the UK. However, it would not be appropriate for the UK to make representations to the US on specific products whilst we are contesting the right of the US to impose any tariffs at all.</p><p> </p><p>We are clear that a tariff war would not be in the interests of UK, EU or US industry. We agree with EU and others that we do not want to see the disputes escalate further. The UK will continue to work closely with the EU on next steps.</p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery","244167","2019-04-25T08:50:30.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121465/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121465/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121465/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-04-11","Ceramics: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on the British ceramic industry of US trade action against EU products.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","244168"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121466","Home Office","false","2019-04-24","<p>The Home Office do not hold this data and therefore cannot provide a <br>response to the request.</p><p>Whilst reported notifiable crimes are recorded and published annually in the crime statistics, recorded and published crimes do not go into the detail of the nationalities of individuals reporting these crimes.</p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2019-04-24T11:57:30.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121466/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121466/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121466/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-04-11","Foreign Nationals: Saudi Arabia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many complaints have been made to the police by Saudi Arabian citizens, or former Saudi Arabian citizens, who felt threatened or sought advice as a result of intimidation they believed was from the Saudi Arabian Government in each year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Crispin Blunt","Reigate","Crispin Blunt","243989"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121467","Department for Transport","false","2019-04-24","<p>Maintenance on Hammersmith Bridge is a matter for the London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham. It is for the Borough to determine their road maintenance priorities. Ministers have not held discussions with the London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham on this matter.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-04-24T14:24:16.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121467/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121467/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121467/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-04-11","Hammersmith Bridge","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has had discussions with representatives of Hammersmith and Fulham Council on their prioritising maintenance of repairs of Hammersmith Bridge; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","244075"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121468","Home Office","false","2019-04-24","<p>The number of enforced returns from the UK by year and country of nationality is published in table rt_02 (returns data tables, volume 1) in ‘Immigration Statistics, year ending December 2018’, available from the GOV.uk website at: <br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/781113/returns1-dec-2018-tables.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/781113/returns1-dec-2018-tables.ods</a></p><p><br>The term 'deportations' refers to a legally-defined subset of returns which are enforced either following a criminal conviction or when it is judged that a person’s removal from the UK is conducive to the public good. Information on those deported is not separately available and therefore the published statistics refer to all enforced returns.</p><p>Information for January to March 2019 will be published in May 2019.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-04-24T12:29:13.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121468/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121468/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121468/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-04-11","Foreign Nationals: Saudi Arabia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many Saudi Arabian citizens were deported from the UK in (a) 2015, (b) 2016,  (c) 2017 and (d) 2018; and how many such citizens have been deported from October 2018 to date.","false","Biography information for Crispin Blunt","Reigate","Crispin Blunt","243990"
