"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121497","Cabinet Office","false","2019-04-24","<p>It remains the Government’s intention to leave the EU with a deal and not participate in European Parliamentary elections.</p><p> </p><p>Returning Officers, who are statutorily independent, work with their local authority to ensure the necessary support and resource are made available to them to deliver elections, including through following guidance issued by the Electoral Commission.</p><p> </p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Torbay","Kevin Foster",,"2019-04-24T12:28:01.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121497/answer","Biography information for Kevin Foster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121497/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1121497/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-04-11","European Parliament: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the readiness and capacity of local authorities to perform their duties relating to the 2019 European Parliament elections.","false","Biography information for Mike Amesbury","Weaver Vale","Mike Amesbury","244195"
